def count_vowels(word):
    sum = 0
    count = 0
    for letter in word:
        if letter in "aeiou":
            count += 1
        sum += count
    return sum

def count_vowels_in_substrings(word):
    return count_vowels(word)
```

    For each position `i` in the string `word`, we calculate the number of vowels in that position. To achieve this, we maintain a `count` variable that increments by 1 every time a vowel is encountered. For each position, this `count` variable holds the total number of vowels found so far, including the current position if the character is a vowel. We accumulate this count onto a `sum` variable, which will store the sum of the number of vowels in all possible substrings ending at the current position. To find the sum of all vowels in all possible substrings of the entire `word`, we just iterate through each character and accumulate the count into the `sum` variable. This algorithm has a linear time complexity of O(n) where n is the length of the input string `word`.

